        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 16 at 5:17PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 516 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sturkie, or 7 miles north of Salem in Fulton County, moving northeast
at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Moko...                           Mammoth Spring...
Sturkie...                        Mammoth Spring State Park...
Fryatt...                         Camp...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 700 PM CDT for eastern and
north central Arkansas.</instruction>
